main event: Two civilians observed an object resembling a jet wing tank trailing a brilliant flame over Munich, Germany on 21 February 1960.
interesting points: The object was light in color and moved at a high rate of speed,The sighting lasted approximately 3 to 5 seconds,The object was seen moving from southeast to northwest,It fell into a clump of trees about 2 miles from the observer,The report indicated that further analysis would not be pursued due to lack of evidence.
sighted object: an object about the size of a jet wing tank emitting yellow glow and blue flame
